<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871210-0037 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Coast Federal Savings andamp; Loan</HL><DD> 12/10/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CFSFTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   Coast Federal Savings andamp; Loan Association said its board took no action Tuesday at a special meeting to consider an offer made by Tampa businessman Hugh F. Culverhouse to acquire the thrift at $18 a share, or about $65.7 million.    Coast Federal, of Sarasota, Fla., said another meeting is set for next Thursday. Meanwhile, the thrift said, its board's financial adviser, Merrill Lynch Capital Markets, is &quot;holding discussions with other parties who have sought information&quot; about the thrift and is exploring other options. </TEXT></DOC>